## Citation Requirements

If you use this software in your research, please cite the following publications:

```bibtex
@article{sayed2021retinal,
    title={Retinal blood vessel segmentation using supervised and unsupervised approaches},
    author={Sayed, Mostafa and others},
    journal={IET Computer Vision},
    year={2021},
    publisher={Institution of Engineering and Technology}
}

@inproceedings{sayed2019aime,
    title={Semi-supervised approach for retinal vessel segmentation},
    author={Sayed, Mostafa and others},
    booktitle={Conference on Artificial Intelligence in Medicine in Europe},
    pages={123--132},
    year={2019},
    organization={Springer}
}

@inproceedings{sayed2019ibpria,
    title={Mixture of supervised and unsupervised approaches for retinal vessel segmentation},
    author={Sayed, Mostafa and others},
    booktitle={Iberian Conference on Pattern Recognition and Image Analysis},
    pages={456--467},
    year={2019},
    organization={Springer}
}
```

## Dataset Acknowledgments

This work uses the following public datasets:

- **DRIVE Database**: Staal, J., et al. "Ridge-based vessel segmentation in color images of the retina." IEEE transactions on medical imaging 23.4 (2004): 501-509.
- **STARE Database**: Hoover, A., et al. "Locating blood vessels in retinal images by piecewise threshold probing of a matched filter response." IEEE Transactions on Medical imaging 19.3 (2000): 203-210.
- **CHASE_DB1**: Owen, C.G., et al. "Measuring retinal vessel tortuosity in 10-year-old children: validation of the Computer-Assisted Image Analysis of the Retina (CAIAR) program." Investigative ophthalmology & visual science 50.5 (2009): 2004-2010.
